        body: '### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nCRA cannot recognize SASS calc(), clamp()  statements well, thus resulting compiler error.\r\n\r\n### Did you try recovering your dependencies?\r\n\r\nI use fresh install npx create-react-app with default setting\r\n\r\n### Which terms did you search for in User Guide?\r\n\r\nsass, scss\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\n  System:\r\n    OS: Windows 10 10.0.19041\r\n    CPU: (2) x64 AMD C-70 APU with Radeon(tm) HD Graphics\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 12.18.4 - C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\node.EXE\r\n    Yarn: Not Found\r\n    npm: 6.14.6 - C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\npm.CMD\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 87.0.4280.141\r\n    Edge: Spartan (44.19041.423.0), Chromium (87.0.664.75)\r\n    Internet Explorer: 11.0.19041.1\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    react: ^17.0.1 => 17.0.1\r\n    react-dom: ^17.0.1 => 17.0.1\r\n    react-scripts: 4.0.1 => 4.0.1\r\n  npmGlobalPackages:\r\n    create-react-app: Not Found\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n(Write your steps here:)\r\n\r\n1. In the App.js, add code:\r\n`\r\nimport Btn from \'./Btn.js\'\r\n`\r\nand add tag:\r\n`\r\n&lt;Btn /&gt;\r\n`\r\n \r\n2. Create Btn.js , then paste this code:\r\n```\r\nimport \'./Btn.scss\';\r\n\r\nexport default function Btn() {\r\n  return (\r\n    <button className="btn"></button>\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Create Btn.scss, then paste this code:\r\n```\r\n.btn {\r\n    --test: calc(\r\n        1\r\n        * clamp(\r\n            1 ,\r\n            ((1 * 1) * 1) ,\r\n            1\r\n        )\r\n    );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n4. npm i sass\r\n5. npm run build\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nthe scss files should produces output like this:\r\n```\r\n.btn {\r\n    --test: calc(1 * clamp(1,((1 * 1) * 1), 1));\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n```\r\nCreating an optimized production build...\r\nFailed to compile.\r\n\r\nLexical error on line 1: Unrecognized text.\r\n  Erroneous area:\r\n1: 1 * clamp( 1 , ((1 * 1) * 1) , 1 )\r\n^...............................^\r\nCompileError: Begins at CSS selector undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Reproducible demo\r\n\r\nfork my github here:\r\nhttps://github.com/heyymarco/react-app-err-css-calc-clamp.git\r\n\r\n### Fix the problem\r\n\r\nIt seem the CRA (or react-scrips) having touble when compressing the output css,\r\nLocated about in postcss or cssnano dependency.\r\n\r\nIs there any configuration for solving this problem? or at least "disable" the css validation check during compression.\r\nI\'m sure my css is valid. Compiled with external sass compiler without problem.\r\nIn my actual project, i even created a more complex css operations using calc(), clamp().\r\nclamp(0, (condition * condition) * 999, 1) is my favorite function because i need many "IF" condition in my css variables.\r\nPlease solve this problem because my projects cannot be continued before this bug has been fixed.',
