        active_lock_reason: null,
        body: '### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nAfter setting up SW precache and clearing cache storage by hand there is no fallback to network and index page is unavailable until SW is unregistered.\r\n\r\n(this could also be an error in workbox modules, not sure)\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\n  current version of create-react-app: 4.0.1\r\n\r\n  System:\r\n    OS: macOS 10.15.7\r\n    CPU: (4) x64 Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-4258U CPU @ 2.40GHz\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 14.13.0 - /usr/local/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.10 - /usr/local/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 7.0.10 - /usr/local/bin/npm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 87.0.4280.141\r\n    Edge: Not Found\r\n    Firefox: 81.0\r\n    Safari: 14.0\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    react: ^17.0.1 => 17.0.1\r\n    react-dom: ^17.0.1 => 17.0.1\r\n    react-scripts: 4.0.1 => 4.0.1\r\n  npmGlobalPackages:\r\n    create-react-app: Not Found\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create new app with `cra-template-pwa` template\r\n2. Register SW in index.js\r\n3. Build app, run `serve -s build`\r\n4. In browser (Chrome), go to Application > Cache > Cache Storage, delete \'workbox-precache-...\'\r\n5. Reload page \r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIndex page falls back to network, cache storage is refilled.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nPage loading fails with \'This site can’t be reached\' error.\r\n\r\n',
        performed_via_github_app: null
