        author_association: 'NONE',
        active_lock_reason: null,
        body: '### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nWhen `yarn start` finishes successfully, it automatically opens Chrome browser and shows running app. If you want to change this behaviour, official CRA docs says to override `BROWSER` environment variable to your desired browser, before the `yarn start` command execution. It works flawlessly. With docker, after it does `yarn start` inside container, it gives an error because is trying to execute Opera browser, which is obviously not possible. And if you try the same without `BROWSER=opera`, it\'s working fine. \r\n\r\nThis is why I think it\'s a bug, because seems that `react-scripts start` check if it is in a headless system and not triggers the browser, but if you overrides BROWSER env var, it doesn\'t check.\r\n\r\n### Environment\r\n\r\n  current version of create-react-app: 4.0.0\r\n  running from /Users/user/.config/yarn/global/node_modules/create-react-app\r\n\r\n  System:\r\n    OS: macOS 10.15.6\r\n    CPU: (8) x64 Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-8257U CPU @ 1.40GHz\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 14.15.0 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v14.15.0/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.10 - /usr/local/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 6.14.8 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v14.15.0/bin/npm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 87.0.4280.141\r\n    Edge: 87.0.664.75\r\n    Firefox: 83.0\r\n    Safari: 13.1.2\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    react: 17.0.1 => 17.0.1 (16.14.0)\r\n    react-dom: 17.0.1 => 17.0.1 (16.14.0)\r\n    react-scripts: 4.0.1 => 4.0.1 \r\n  npmGlobalPackages:\r\n    create-react-app: Not Found\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Fresh create-react-app install.\r\n2. Create a .env with `BROWSER=opera` inside\r\n2. Command `yarn start` -> OK\r\n3. Dockerizating app with simple `Dockerfile`:\r\n```\r\n# base image\r\nFROM node:14.15-slim\r\n# set working directory\r\nWORKDIR /app\r\n# copy package.json and lock to ensure correct versions\r\nCOPY package.json yarn.lock ./\r\n# install node modules\r\nRUN yarn --non-interactive --frozen-lockfile\r\n# add app to container\r\nCOPY . /app\r\n# start app in dev mode\r\nCMD yarn start\r\n```\r\n4. Running the docker\r\n5. Error\r\n```\r\n Starting the development server...\r\nevents.js:292\r\nthrow er; // Unhandled \'error\' event\r\n^\r\nError: spawn opera ENOENT\r\n     at Process.ChildProcess._handle.onexit (internal/child_process.js:269:19)\r\n     at onErrorNT (internal/child_process.js:465:16)\r\n     at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:80:21)\r\n Emitted \'error\' event on ChildProcess instance at:\r\n     at Process.ChildProcess._handle.onexit (internal/child_process.js:275:12)\r\n     at onErrorNT (internal/child_process.js:465:16)\r\n     at processTicksAndRejections (internal/process/task_queues.js:80:21) {\r\n   errno: -2,\r\n   code: \'ENOENT\',\r\n   syscall: \'spawn opera\',\r\n   path: \'opera\',\r\n...\r\n```\r\n',
